# 6. いざ目の前にしたら

Saki: Thanks for waiting! Sorry I'm late—
Honami: Oh, Saki!
Ichika: Saki, there you are!
Shiho: Did you see my message?
Saki: Your message...? You said you're gonna start eating without me...
Shiho: That's not important. I mean the one after that about Mr. Shindo.
Saki: Mr. Shindo...? Wait, does that mean...?
Ichika: Yeah, we just received word. So...
Ichika: He wants to meet with us about making our debut!
Saki: What...?
Ichika: I did get a little worried there for a second, but actually hearing back... My jaw was on the floor!
Honami: This means we have a real chance at going pro, right...?!
Shiho: It's so nice to see someone finally recognizing our music...
Saki: W-We did it...!
Saki: It's really happening! We're going pro!
Honami: We should reply as soon as we can. As for when we're going to meet him...
Saki: (I'm still really scared...)
Saki: (Even though I couldn't wait to hear back from Mr. Shindo... I should be happy that his company wants to sign us...)
Saki: (We even decided as a group that we're going to deal with our fears...)
Shiho: But I believe that we'll figure out a way to overcome all that.
Shiho: So, don't worry.
Saki: (What am I supposed to do...?)
Shiho: Anyway, nice work today. See you all tomorrow.
Saki: Okay, bye bye!
Saki: (We're meeting about our deal this weekend...)
Saki: (Am I really gonna be okay...? Will I stop feeling scared by then...?)
Saki: (I mean, the others said they're scared too. I was hoping that these feelings would go away after a while...)
Saki: (But I guess that's just not gonna happen...)
Saki: (I'm really worried... But I just have to be brave and move for—)
???: Hm...? Ms. Tenma, is that you?
Saki: Huh...?
Shindo: What a coincidence. Are you on your way home from that rehearsal studio?
Saki: M-Mr. Shindo...!
Saki: Yes, we just finished practicing there. We also saw the message you sent us this afternoon...
Saki: The others couldn't believe that we're actually gonna get signed to a label! Everyone felt more motivated than usual during practice today!
Shindo: Oh, is that so? I'm glad you're all enthusiastic about our proposed deal.
Saki: Yes, we're very enthusiastic! I mean, it's been our dream to go pro together!
Saki: The others said that they're looking forward to our meeting...
Shindo: So, Ms. Tenma, how about you?
Saki: What...?
Shindo: You said that “the others” are looking forward to it...
Shindo: But how do you feel?
Saki: I...
Saki: I-I'm really happy...! Because we've all been pursuing the same dream...
Saki: For so...very long...we've wanted to become professional musicians... So, um...
Saki: In order to get more and more people to listen to our music...
Shindo: ...
Shindo: Would you mind if we talked for a bit...?
Saki: What?
Shindo: It's not too late for you to be out yet, so how about I buy you a drink?
Saki: What?! But I'm a minor!
Shindo: Hahaha. I didn't mean anything alcoholic. Just a cup of tea.
Saki: B-But... I feel bad about you paying for me...
Shindo: Don't worry, this one's on my company. Also...
Shindo: I may be able to help if there's something weighing on your mind.
Saki: Oh...
Saki: (Yeah, Mr. Shindo's probably met tons of people like me until now. He might be able to tell me what I should do in this situation...)
Saki: (But what if he thinks, “What a downer! Maybe we shouldn't sign her”...?!)
Shindo: Alright, let's go.
Saki: Huh...?!
Saki: W-Wait for me...!
Shindo: I see.
Shindo: You feel stronger about continuing to make music with your friends than you do about having your music heard by others...
Shindo: And you're worried if it's okay to feel that way, and afraid about the prospect of signing with a label.
Saki: Y-Yes...
Saki: (Geez, I didn't feel like I could hide anything from him and ended up telling him everything...)
Shindo: Well, if I'm going to be honest...
Shindo: I agree with Ms. Hinomori. There's nothing wrong with wanting to stay together.
Saki: Oh...
Saki: O-Okay...
Shindo: But hearing that didn't really make you feel any better, right?
Saki: ...! I mean...
Shindo: Would you mind if I told you a little story?
Saki: A story?
Shindo: Yes.
Shindo: It's about a band you'd find anywhere else that became the talk of the town for a while some time back...
